ADDITIONAL TERMS — CITATION AND ACADEMIC LICENSING

The following additional terms supplement the PolyForm Strict
License 1.0.0 above and are binding on all users of this software.

1. CITATION REQUIREMENT

   Any published work — including but not limited to journal articles,
   conference papers, technical reports, theses, dissertations,
   preprints, posters, presentations, or public-facing documentation —
   that uses this software or presents results produced by this
   software must include the following citation:

   Rudder, J. & Rudder, A. (2025). pmtvs: Precision Mathematical
   Toolkit for Validated Signals. https://github.com/pmtvs/pmtvs

   Failure to cite constitutes a violation of these license terms.

2. ACADEMIC USE TIERS

   a) Individual Academic Use — FREE

      Students (undergraduate, graduate, postdoctoral), individual
      researchers, and educators may use this software at no cost
      for personal research, coursework, thesis work, and teaching,
      provided no grant or external funding exceeding $100,000 USD
      (or equivalent) directly supports the work in which this
      software is used. Citation is required per Section 1.

   b) Funded Research Use — ACADEMIC RESEARCH LICENSE REQUIRED

      Use of this software in research supported by grant funding,
      contracts, or institutional funding exceeding $100,000 USD
      (or equivalent) from any source — including but not limited
      to federal agencies (NIH, NSF, DOE, DOD, NASA), state agencies,
      private foundations, or industry sponsors — requires a paid
      Academic Research License.

      Contact: licensing@pmtvs.dev

      Citation is required per Section 1.

   c) University or Institutional Site License

      Departments or institutions seeking unlimited use across
      multiple researchers and labs may purchase a Site License.

      Contact: licensing@pmtvs.dev

3. COMMERCIAL USE

   Any use in connection with commercial activity — including but
   not limited to use in commercial products, commercial services,
   consulting engagements, internal commercial tooling, or any
   activity intended to generate revenue — requires a separate
   Commercial License.

   Contact: licensing@pmtvs.dev

4. EVALUATION USE

   Any organization may use this software for evaluation,
   proof-of-concept, and technical assessment purposes for
   a period not exceeding 90 days. Evaluation use must not
   process production data or generate revenue. Continued
   use beyond 90 days requires the appropriate license per
   Sections 2 or 3.

   Contact: licensing@pmtvs.dev

